kdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533361\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104whv1665702905118.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/whv1665702905118.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/whv1665702905118.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"whv1665702905118\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Null Values and Included Uniface Entities in XML\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Null fields are saved into XML streams as empty elements. This means that a null field is indistinguishable from an empty string. When an empty element is loaded into a numeric field it is converted into a zero numeric value.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"whv1665702905118__section_yg1_yjz_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d222455e51\">Null Values and Absent Elements</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"whv1665702905118__p_d38684e1_d38685e1_d38686e1\">Fields in occurrences created by\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">xmlload</span> that do not have an XML stream element mapped to them are\n        treated as null fields. That is, when <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reconnect</span> (or\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span>) merges the occurrences created from the XML stream\n        with database occurrences, the null fields do not overwrite the database fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"whv1665702905118__p_d38687e1_d38688e1_d38689e1\">Included entities are an exception to this behavior.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"whv1665702905118__section_mt1_1kz_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d222455e72\">Included Entities</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"whv1665702905118__p_d38693e1_d38694e1_d38695e1\">When reconnecting disconnected record sets, occurrences\n        of included entities are completely overwritten by the data in the disconnected record.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"whv1665702905118__p_d38696e1_d38697e1_d38698e1\">Therefore, if any data from an included entity is\n        required in an XML stream, it is essential to include all the fields of the included entity\n        in the XML stream.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"whv1665702905118__note_xv2_bkz_pcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If there is no element in the XML stream for a given\n        field of an included entity, then that field is emptied. This means that if all the data of\n        an included entity is not placed in an XML stream, data loss can occur when the XML stream\n        is reconnected. This restriction applies to only included entities.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gpq1665702699272.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>XML Streams</a><p>XML streams are data streams using an XML format. They enable loosely coupled connections between components, and provide a standardized format for data transport between components. Uniface can transfer field data and data relationships via XML stream parameters. It can also attach processing information to data in an XML stream to allow the data state to be transported with the data.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533361\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533361\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Null Values and Included Uniface Entities in XML Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Null Values and Included Uniface Entities in XML Null fields are saved into XML streams as empty elements. This means that a null field is indistinguishable from an empty string. When an empty element is loaded into a numeric field it is converted into a zero numeric value. Null Values and Absent Elements Fields in occurrences created by xmlload that do not have an XML stream element mapped to them are treated as null fields. That is, when reconnect (or retrieve/reconnect ) merges the occurrences created from the XML stream with database occurrences, the null fields do not overwrite the database fields. Included entities are an exception to this behavior. Included Entities When reconnecting disconnected record sets, occurrences of included entities are completely overwritten by the data in the disconnected record. Therefore, if any data from an included entity is required in an XML stream, it is essential to include all the fields of the included entity in the XML stream. Note: If there is no element in the XML stream for a given field of an included entity, then that field is emptied. This means that if all the data of an included entity is not placed in an XML stream, data loss can occur when the XML stream is reconnected. This restriction applies to only included entities. Related Links XML Streams XML streams are data streams using an XML format. They enable loosely coupled connections between components, and provide a standardized format for data transport between components. Uniface can transfer field data and data relationships via XML stream parameters. It can also attach processing information to data in an XML stream to allow the data state to be transported with the data. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}